# PostUp ðŸ“±

A simple Expo (React Native) app that fetches posts from a public API and displays them in a scrollable list with a fixed header and footer.

---

## ðŸ›  Tech Stack

- [Expo](https://expo.dev/)
- [React Native](https://reactnative.dev/)
- [TypeScript](https://www.typescriptlang.org/)
- [NativeWind](https://www.nativewind.dev/) (Utility-first styling for React Native)
- Functional components + Hooks

---

## ðŸ“¦ Setup Instructions

1. **Clone the repo**

```bash
git clone https://github.com/your-username/postup.git
cd postup
```

2. **Install dependencies**

```bash
npm install
```

3. **Start the Expo project**

```bash
npm start
```

> Or use platform-specific scripts:
>
> - Android: `npm run android`
> - iOS: `npm run ios`
> - Web: `npm run web`

---

## ðŸ¤” Assumptions & Limitations

- Only one screen (Home) is included.
- Posts are read-only; no post creation/editing functionality.
- No pagination or infinite scroll.
- The mock API is public and unauthenticated, so no auth flow is handled.
